1
00:00:36,620 --> 00:00:37,620
Now, let's move on to

2
00:00:37,620 --> 00:00:40,040
a cultural museum that I really like,

3
00:00:40,040 --> 00:00:42,000
called the Alhambra Palace.

4
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:44,700
It's located in Granada, southern Spain.

5
00:00:44,700 --> 00:00:47,700
In 1984, it was included
in the World Cultural Heritage List.

6
00:00:48,160 --> 00:00:50,160
Generally, Spanish architecture

7
00:00:50,160 --> 00:00:51,830
is mostly Catholic.

8
00:00:51,830 --> 00:00:55,620
But the Alhambra Palace
is in Eastern Islamic style.

9
00:00:55,620 --> 00:00:57,620
This is because, in 711 AD,

10
00:00:57,620 --> 00:00:59,870
the Moors led the Arabs

11
00:00:59,870 --> 00:01:01,330
to invade the Iberian Peninsula,

12
00:01:01,330 --> 00:01:03,700
which is now Spain and Portugal.

13
00:01:03,700 --> 00:01:06,040
Then, Muhammad I

14
00:01:06,040 --> 00:01:07,620
built the Alhambra Palace,

15
00:01:07,620 --> 00:01:09,870
mainly as a defensive fortress.

16
00:01:10,200 --> 00:01:12,370
It wasn't until 1492,

17
00:01:12,370 --> 00:01:14,330
after Spain completed the Reconquista,

18
00:01:14,330 --> 00:01:16,120
that the Moors were driven out.

19
00:01:16,120 --> 00:01:17,080
Since then,

20
00:01:17,080 --> 00:01:19,750
the Alhambra Palace has been a deserted

21
00:01:19,750 --> 00:01:21,330
and abandoned site for centuries.

22
00:01:21,700 --> 00:01:23,830
Does anyone have any questions so far?

23
00:01:24,660 --> 00:01:25,830
No.

24
00:01:30,500 --> 00:01:31,370
What's wrong?

25
00:01:31,750 --> 00:01:33,450
Do you dislike Spain

26
00:01:33,450 --> 00:01:35,290
or the Reconquista?

27
00:01:38,250 --> 00:01:39,660
I just don't like history.

28
00:01:41,200 --> 00:01:43,620
History is merely
a grim record of invasions

29
00:01:45,620 --> 00:01:47,500
about the conquers,

30
00:01:47,500 --> 00:01:49,160
new borders,

31
00:01:50,120 --> 00:01:51,950
new nations,

32
00:01:52,370 --> 00:01:54,160
and new territories.

33
00:02:01,830 --> 00:02:02,750
What?

34
00:02:04,040 --> 00:02:05,250
Did I say something wrong?

35
00:02:07,330 --> 00:02:08,700
Not really,

36
00:02:08,700 --> 00:02:09,870
but...

37
00:02:10,290 --> 00:02:13,790
It's precisely these movements
and advancements

38
00:02:14,750 --> 00:02:16,450
that broke down walls

39
00:02:17,500 --> 00:02:18,750
and allowed love

40
00:02:18,750 --> 00:02:20,290
to spread throughout the world.

41
00:02:22,370 --> 00:02:23,540
And

42
00:02:24,370 --> 00:02:27,500
because of these so-called boundaries,

43
00:02:27,950 --> 00:02:29,660
we get the chance
to enter each other's worlds

44
00:02:29,660 --> 00:02:31,290
and understand one another.

45
00:02:32,040 --> 00:02:34,790
So, do you think
I'm invading your world now,

46
00:02:38,500 --> 00:02:40,450
or are you invading mine?

47
00:02:48,450 --> 00:02:50,250
I just don't like history.

48
00:02:54,200 --> 00:02:55,830
And then, they left it abandoned
for centuries,

49
00:02:55,830 --> 00:02:57,950
until 1828,

50
00:02:57,950 --> 00:03:00,840
when King Ferdinand VII of Spain

51
00:03:00,840 --> 00:03:01,840
began restoration...

52
